class HouseBuilding {
    public static int getMinimum(String[] area) {
        int rows = area.length;
        int cols = area[0].length();
        int minHeight = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int maxHeight = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
                int currentHeight = Integer.parseInt(area[i].substring(j, j + 1));
                minHeight = Math.min(minHeight, currentHeight);
                maxHeight = Math.max(maxHeight, currentHeight);
            }
        }
        int targetHeight = (minHeight + maxHeight) / 2;
        int totalEffort = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
                int currentHeight = Integer.parseInt(area[i].substring(j, j + 1));
                totalEffort += Math.abs(currentHeight - targetHeight);
            }
        }
        return totalEffort;
    }
}
```
This program follows the given problem statement and method signature. It first finds the minimum and maximum height of the area and calculates the target height as the average of the minimum and maximum height. Then it iterates through the area, calculating the effort required to level each square meter by taking the absolute value of the difference between the current height and the target height, and adding it to a total effort variable. Finally, the program returns the total effort required to level the entire area.

